<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1198] confine all solrconfig.xml parsing to SolrConfig.java</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1198</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently , xpath evaluations are spread across Solr code. It would be cleaner if if can do it all in one place . All the parsing can be done in SolrConfig.java&lt;br/&gt;
another problem with the current design is that we are not able to benefit from re-use of solrconfig object across cores. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12427022">SOLR-1198</key>
            <summary>confine all solrconfig.xml parsing to SolrConfig.java</summary>
